Here are the MSTest attributes and patterns for each scenario:

**1. Windows-only (registry)** — `[OSCondition]` (MSTest 3.10+)
```csharp
[TestMethod]
[OSCondition(OperatingSystems.Windows)]
public void Registry_ReadsExpectedValue()
{
    var value = Registry.GetValue(@"HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\MyApp", "Setting", null);
    Assert.IsNotNull(value);
}
```

**2. Skip in CI (local GPU required)** — `[CICondition]`
```csharp
[TestMethod]
[CICondition(ConditionMode.Exclude)]
public void RenderFrame_ProducesExpectedOutput()
{
    var result = GpuRenderer.RenderFrame();
    Assert.IsNotNull(result);
}
```

**3. Flaky weather API** — `[Retry]` (MSTest 3.9+)
```csharp
[TestMethod]
[Retry(3)]
[Timeout(10000)]
public async Task WeatherApi_ReturnsForecast(TestContext testContext)
{
    var forecast = await _weatherClient.GetForecastAsync(testContext.CancellationToken);
    Assert.IsNotNull(forecast);
}
```
> Use `[Retry]` only for genuinely flaky external dependencies — not to mask race conditions or shared-state bugs.

**4. Temp file cleanup** — `[TestCleanup]` + `IDisposable`
```csharp
[TestClass]
public sealed class FileProcessorTests : IDisposable
{
    private readonly string _tempFile;

    public FileProcessorTests()
    {
        _tempFile = Path.GetTempFileName();
    }

    [TestMethod]
    public void ProcessFile_WritesExpectedContent()
    {
        FileProcessor.Process(_tempFile);
        Assert.Contains("expected", File.ReadAllText(_tempFile));
    }

    // Runs even if the test fails
    public void Dispose()
    {
        if (File.Exists(_tempFile))
            File.Delete(_tempFile);
    }
}
```

**You can combine them too:**
```csharp
[TestMethod]
[OSCondition(OperatingSystems.Windows)]
[CICondition(ConditionMode.Exclude)]
[Retry(2)]
public void GpuRegistry_WindowsLocalOnly() { /* ... */ }
```

All of these require **MSTest 3.9+** (for `[Retry]`) or **3.10+** (for `[OSCondition]`/`[CICondition]`). Ensure your project references a recent enough version.
